<collectingRegion id="AE158DE9FFA5FFFBF839AD7082A5FDDC" box="[588,704,542,568]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
include Ubatuba and São Sebastião (
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFA5FFFBFE1AAD7085F2FDDC" author="Mistakidis, M. N. &amp; Neiva, G. D. S." box="[1135,1431,542,568]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="434 - 434" refId="ref70423" refString="Mistakidis, M. N. &amp; Neiva, G. D. S. (1966) New Records of the Shrimps Hymenopenaeus tropicalis and Parapenaeus americanus from Brazil. Nature, 211 (5047), 434 - 434. https: // doi. org / 10.1038 / 211434 a 0" type="journal article" year="1966">Mistakidis &amp; Neiva 1966</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFA5FFFBFAE2AD2C8177FDB8" author="Pires, A. M. S." box="[151,274,578,604]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="63 - 76" refId="ref73888" refString="Pires, A. M. S. (1992) Structure and dynamics of benthic megafauna on the continental shelf offshore of Ubatuba, southeastern, Brazil. Marine Ecology Progress Series, 86, 63 - 76. https: // doi. org / 10.3354 / meps 086063" type="journal article" year="1992">Pires 1992</bibRefCitation>
). However, information about the collection where the specimens were deposited was not provided. The occurrence of this species in 
<collectingRegion id="AE158DE9FFA5FFFBFBA3AD088223FD64" box="[470,582,614,640]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
seems doubtful, since we could not examine specimens deposited in any collection, neither obtain individuals in our samples. There are some gaps in the Brazilian coast distribution (from 
<collectingRegion id="AE158DE9FFA5FFFBFF01ADE48130FD2C" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Norte" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Rio Grande do Norte</collectingRegion>
to 
<collectingRegion id="AE158DE9FFA5FFFBFB0EADC08279FD2C" box="[379,540,686,712]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
and from 
<collectingRegion id="AE158DE9FFA5FFFBF8E7ADC08361FD2C" box="[658,772,686,712]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
to 
<collectingRegion id="AE158DE9FFA5FFFBF95FADC0839AFD2D" box="[810,1023,686,713]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
) (see references above). In addition, 
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFA5FFFBFAE2ADBC8137FD09" author="D'Incao, F." box="[151,338,722,749]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refId="ref59841" refString="D'Incao, F. (1995 a) Taxonomia, padroes distribucionais e ecologicos dos Dendrobranchiata (Crustacea: Decapoda) do Brasil e Atlantico Ocidental. PhD Thesis, Universidade Federal do Parana, Brasil, 365 pp." type="book" year="1995">D’Incao (1995a)</bibRefCitation>
argues that the reason of these gaps is the difficulty on sampling deep waters, since most of the records of this species occur in depths greater than 
<specimenCount id="7AD78882FFA5FFFBF8A2AD988343FCF4" box="[727,806,758,784]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="generic">
<quantity id="AB29EEEEFFA5FFFBF8A2AD988347FCF4" box="[727,802,758,784]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" unit="m" value="100.0">100 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
Such depth was not our main target during our surveys. There is 16S sequence available on GenBank (
<accessionNumber id="7382DEE8FFA5FFFBF8E8AC748371FCD0" box="[669,788,794,820]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/JX403849" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">JX403849</accessionNumber>
) of a specimen from Gulf of 
<collectingRegion id="AE158DE9FFA5FFFBFE2DAC7484B5FCD0" box="[1112,1232,794,820]" country="Mexico" name="Distrito Federal" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Mexico by</collectingRegion>
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFA5FFFBFEA2AC748141FCBC" author="Bracken-Grissom, H. D. &amp; Felder, D. L. &amp; Vollmer, N. L. &amp; Martin, J. W. &amp; Crandall, K. A." pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="2367 - 2373" refId="ref55322" refString="Bracken-Grissom, H. D., Felder, D. L., Vollmer, N. L., Martin, J. W. &amp; Crandall, K. A. (2012) Phylogenetics links monster larva to deep-sea shrimp. Ecology and Evolution, 2 (10), 2367 - 2373. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / ece 3.347" type="journal article" year="2012">
Bracken-Grissom 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFA5FFFBFAE2AC5180AAFCBC" box="[151,207,830,856]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">et al.</emphasis>
(2012)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6C6E430BFFA5FFFBFAE2ACC78222FC20" blockId="17.[151,583,937,964]" box="[151,583,937,964]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
